edu.csupomona.cs.cs141.prog_assgmnt_4

Class Appointment

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.csupomona.cs.cs141.prog_assgmnt_4.Appointment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class Appointment
extends Object
implements Serializable
    The Appointment object is made to keep track of the appointments set up in the vet office. Each appointment has a date, a time, and a client, which will be the animal, and not the owner.
    Author:
    David Scianni
    See Also:

    • Field Detail

      • serialVersionUID

        private static final long serialVersionUID
        This is the default serial ID for the Appointment Object.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • date

        String date
        This String will keep track of the date of the appointment. It will be set up in the year/month/day fashion.

      • time

        String time
        This String will keep track of the time of the appointment. It will be set up in the ##:##am/pm fashion.

      • client

        Animal client
        This is the Animal that the appointment is for. We keep track of the animal rather than the owner, since an owner could possibly have more than one animal.
